com.tractrac.model.lib.impl.data

Class PositionCompressed

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tractrac.model.lib.api.attachment.AbstractAttachable
      • com.tractrac.model.lib.impl.data.PositionCompressed
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IAttachable, IPosition, ITimeData, IGeoCoordinate, com.tractrac.util.lib.api.serialize.ISerializable

    public class PositionCompressed
extends AbstractAttachable
implements IPosition
    Encapsulates position data: longitude, latitude, height, speed, and direction.

    The precision maintained when packing/unpacking position data using this class is:

    • Longitude and latitude: From -214 to 214 in steps of 0.0000001.
    • Height: Represented by a float.
    • Speed: From 0 to 3276.7 in steps of 0.1. If the value is outside this interval, it is converted to the closest value in the interval.
    • Direction: From 0 to 359.9 in steps of 0.1 (modulo 360 is first applied).
    Author:
    Jan Marthedal Rasmussen
